Subject: [PATCH 3/3] drivers/perf: convert sysfs sprintf family to sysfs_emit
Date:   Wed, 17 Mar 2021 17:41:51 +0800
Message-ID: <1615974111-45601-4-git-send-email-liuqi115@huawei.com>
X-Mailer: git-send-email 2.8.1
In-Reply-To: <1615974111-45601-1-git-send-email-liuqi115@huawei.com>
References: <1615974111-45601-1-git-send-email-liuqi115@huawei.com>
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain
X-Originating-IP: [10.67.165.24]
X-CFilter-Loop: Reflected
Precedence: bulk
List-ID: <linux-kernel.vger.kernel.org>
X-Mailing-List: linux-kernel@vger.kernel.org

sprintf does not know the PAGE_SIZE maximum of the temporary buffer
used for sysfs content and it's possible to overrun the buffer length.

Use sysfs_emit() function to ensures that no overrun is done.

Signed-off-by: Qi Liu <liuqi115@huawei.com>
---
